[[File:Jari Sarasvuo 2.jpg|thumb|Jari Sarasvuo in 2013]]
'''Jari Sarasvuo''' (born ''Jari Heinonen''; 12 June 1965 in [[Turku]]) is the founder, chief owner and CEO of [[Trainers' House]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.iltasanomat.fi/kotimaa/Jari%20Sarasvuo%20T%C3%A4m%C3%A4%20on%20ty%C3%B6el%C3%A4m%C3%A4ni%20surullisin%20p%C3%A4iv%C3%A4/art-1288334782018.html|title=Jari Sarasvuo: "Tämä on työelämäni surullisin päivä" - Ilta-Sanomat|last=Pimiä|first=Katarina|date=25 February 2009|work=[[Ilta-Sanomat]]|language=Finnish|accessdate=1 June 2011}}</ref> a [[Finland|Finnish]] company that arranges training and lectures particularly for marketing topics.

Sarasvuo has worked as an [[editing|editor]] and [[chief editor]] in several [[magazine]]s and also in [[Helsinki]]'s [[Radio City (Finland)|Radio City]]. His first publicity was as a host in a talk show on the Finnish channel [[MTV3]] in the 1990s. After leaving jobs in television, he has worked as a lecturer and as a motivational coach, also publishing six books on the same topic. One of his famous concepts is the "inner hero" (''sisäinen sankari''), and he has also coined the term ''huomiotalous'' ("attention economy"), describing the central role of publicity in the today's economy.

Sarasvuo studied business administration, but has not finished the degree. In his conscript duty, he was an editor of the army newspaper ''[[Ruotuväki]]'', and was promoted to Second Lieutenant (''[[vänrikki]]'') in reserve.

Sarasvuo was the host in ''[[Diili]]'', a localized version of ''[[The Apprentice (TV series)|The Apprentice]]''. Sarasvuo has often appeared in publicity and his company hosted [[Bill Clinton]]'s lecture in [[Tampere]]. Sarasvuo owns about a third of Trainer's House, and if evaluated, the stock is valued at some 34 million [[euro]]s (January 2008). He has also contributed to charity in the form of providing [[microcredit]] and taking part in a project to support [[Bangladesh]]i women to become [[entrepreneur]]s.

Sarasvuo has been married to former cross-country skier [[Virpi Sarasvuo]] (née Kuitunen) since 2010. They have one child, a daughter born in 2011. Sarasvuo also has two children from a previous relationship.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.iltalehti.fi/viihde/2011032713444135_vi.shtml |title=Virpi ja Jari Sarasvuo saivat tytön |date=March 27, 2011 |website=Iltalehti.fi |language=fi |access-date=2018-03-03}}</ref>

