{{Portal|Cooperatives}}
The '''Network of Bay Area Worker Cooperatives''' ('''NoBAWC''' ''- pronounced "No Boss"'') is a network of [[worker cooperative]]s dedicated to building [[workplace democracy]] in the [[San Francisco Bay Area]].<ref>Gans, Lydia. [http://www.berkeleydailyplanet.com/issue/2005-07-29/article/21968?headline=Be-Your-Own-Boss-Join-a-Collective-By-LYDIA-GANS-Special-to-the-Planet&status=301 Be Your Own Boss, Join a Collective.] ''The Berkeley Daily Planet.'' 29 July 2005.</ref>
NoBAWC was founded in September 1994 when workers representing nine worker cooperatives met to address their isolation and to build a worker cooperative movement in the region. Twelve years later, NoBAWC comprises 30 dues-paying workplaces with a paid staff. NoBAWC is a member of the [[United States Federation of Worker Cooperatives]].
